			<ns0:name>jvo...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/102292187274959663599/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
The voronoi test in our repo. depends on the newlib random number generator for colors and for the checksum of those colors.

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
If we switch over to glibc (completely or partially), and it happens to have a different implementation of the RNG, our checksums would not match.

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
As Nicholas proposed, make the test more self-contained and have its own simple RNG.
